I've ridden by this "park" since the Metro Gold Line cane on line and it was known as the Cornfield, I've attended Concerts, and other events here, but FINALLY, after years of renovations and digging and setting up bridges to nowhere - trust me, they may go nowhere, but you get an elevated view if the surrounding area and of course of DTLA - this gem of green space just a stones throw from the Gold Line's Chinatown station is set to open soon.  Read on.  A Beautiful New Park Is About to Open Just East of Chinatown  Los Angeles State Historic Park has been in the works for over ten years.  March 24, 2017. Written by: Thomas Harlander. Your link: http://www.lamag.com/culturefiles/beautiful-new-park-open-just-east-chinatown/  It’s true that Los Angeles has some magnificent parks (we see you Vista Hermosa), but there are still many areas of the city that are criminally short on green space. That’s why the nearly completed Los Angeles State Historic Park is such a blessing. The 32-acre island of sweet, sweet nature in the middle of one of the city’s denser areas (near Chinatown and Lincoln Heights, just off the Gold Line) has been in the works since 2006. It’s finally opening on April 22.  The space occupies the site of a train depot built by the #southernpacificrailroad in 1875. It’s the place where countless transplants first set foot in Los Angeles. Five years after acquiring the site in 2001, the California Department of Parks and Recreation opened the grassy expanse to the public. In 2014, though, the state closed it down to transform the area into a beautifully designed park with walking paths, elevated bridges, wetland space, plenty of shade trees, and a restaurant and beer garden.  The park’s grand opening festivities kick off at 10 a.m. on April 22, and will feature musical performances and food trucks

the #Crossfit open is done. It was a 'war' for me, injuries, stress, but I managed to go ahead anyway. For sure I couldn't do this alone..too much even for me! I had fear, I'm not ashamed to say it (I'm still thinking about the hospital sometimes 😂). But thanks to you I was able to manage it and move on with pain, no motivation and various problems. thanks to who have judged and motivated us @crossfit2010 @alexanfuso @travsbits Louisa and Karl, who 'repaired' us @benjimen.89  I really appreciated your support, especially because both (me and sam) are the most break balls ever with our complaints and our many problems every time before start a workout 😂. what I learn from this open? to stay positive, work hard, make IT happen! Feeling blessed to be able to enjoy the little things in life like this one.  This period will always remain in my memories, I can say I was happy, despite everything! My journey is almost at the end (for real this time,maybe 😂) , I want to say just Thank You. Wherever I will be, you must know that you have someone you can count on, I'll be ready for you 💪! (and one day I'll speak a good english, I promise)

Це, фактично, єдині масштабні змагання найвищого рівня зі спортивної гімнастики, які відбуваються в нашій країні. На турнірі будуть пристуні делегації з багатьох країн світу, серед них - еліта спортивної гімнастики: олімпійські чемпіони, чемпіони світу. На ювілейний турнір, Палац спорту готується прийняти більше восьми тисяч гостей. Крім вже знайомих нам представників Грузії, Німеччини, Єгипту, Словенії, Білорусі, Молдови, Фінляндії ми також чекаємо учасників з інших країн світу.  https://welcomua.wordpress.com/2017/… @stella_zakharova #squat #sweet #selfie #sea #style #streetstyle #studio #sydney #summer #sun #surprise #singer #sister #song #sport #spring #spb #ss #sfs #sf #show #shellac #sky #sketch #sketchbook #school #sneakers #snapseed #smile

Berkshire pork belly, pumped full of hot and cold smoke, fried crispy and served with a soft yolked fried egg. The green apple chutney and limes I thought would be weird but they really worked beautifully. Some vinegar in the chutney added acidity to its sweetness for balance. If it wasn't in such a unique spot I'd be eating this many mornings this year 👊

The Sydney Opera House is a multi-venue performing arts centre in Sydney, Australia. It is one of the 20th century's most famous and distinctive buildings.[3] Designed by Danish architect Jørn Utzon, the building was formally opened on 20 October 1973[4] after a gestation beginning with Utzon's 1957 selection as winner of an international design competition. The government of New South Wales, led by the premier, Joseph Cahill, authorised work to begin in 1958 with Utzon directing construction. The government's decision to build Utzon's design is often overshadowed by circumstances that followed, including cost and scheduling overruns as well as the architect's ultimate resignation.[5 The building and its surrounds occupy the whole of Bennelong Point on Sydney Harbour, between Sydney Cove and Farm Cove, adjacent to the Sydney central business district and the Royal Botanic Gardens, and close by the Sydney Harbour Bridge. Though its name suggests a single venue, the building comprises multiple performance venues which together are among the busiest[citation needed] performing arts centres – hosting well over 1,500 performances annually, attended by more than 1.2 million people.[6] Performances are presented by numerous performing artists, including four resident companies: Opera Australia, The Australian Ballet, the Sydney Theatre Company and the Sydney Symphony Orchestra. As one of the most popular visitor attractions in Australia, more than eight million people visit the site annually, and approximately 350,000 visitors take a guided tour of the building each year.[7] The building is managed by the Sydney Opera House Trust, an agency of the New South Wales State Government. @josiemarancosmetics product review: Josie Maran 100% pure argan oil is a multitasking wonder product, this oil can be used to hydrate, protect and heal nails, hair and skin. This oil is used for so many things, a drop is also enough to smooth out hair or soften dry and hard cuticles. Argan oil has a number of benefits when used on hair. It can act as a moisturiser for the scalp to fight dandruff and dry scalp or it even can be used as a hair mask! It can also promote the growth of healthy, strong hair as opposed to thin, brittle hair. It can even undo some of the damage done through chemical treatments and dyes, and can be used to treat split ends. For other users I also recommend patting it over the neck as well as massaging it onto rough and dry skin patches like the elbows, knees, hands and feet. You can also add a drop of this argan oil into your daily moisturizer prior to application to boost its moisturizing effect or even add a few drops of the Aragon oil to your foundation to help give that nice radiant dewy effect! This Oil doesn't leave that greasy oily effect which I absolutely love! When my skin is feeling really dry and flaky I add a few drops off this and massage it into my face onto my lips, lashes and eyebrows to promote growth for my lashes and brows and hydration for my lips over night only waking up the next morning to radiant plump soft hydrated skin! I swear by this product it's so versatile and you will not regret especially in the winter season!! 10일째 오늘도 소은이 사진으로 시작. 여행의 막바지지만 소은이는 조금 더 성장한 것 같다. 물론 떼도 늘었다 ㅋ. 오늘은 날씨가 그나마 괜찮아서 로얄 보타닉가든을 향한다. 가는 길에 울루물루 선착장에 큰 배와 바다에 인접한 수영장이 보인다. 미세스맥쿼리로드를 따라서 걸어가다보면 미세스맥쿼리체어가 보인다. 중국인들이 너무 많아서 체어에서의 사진은 생략ㅋ. 지나서 조금만 더 가게 되면 하버브릿지와 오페라하우스가 동시에 보는 멋진 나이스 뷰를 즐길 수 있다. 벤치에서 잠시간의 여유를 즐긴 후 오페라하우스로 가다가 넓디 넓은 잔디밭 나무 밑에서 사색을 즐기는 한 사람이 있었는데 그 모습이 영화와도 같아서 사진을 찍어 본다. #pretty #adorable #baby #베이비스타그램 #여행스타그램 #soeun #sydney #macquariechair #royalbotanicgardens #operahouse #harbourbridge #niceview

🐒Hanging Out For Shoulder Health🐒 ---------------------------------- The shoulder joint has the most range of motion out of any joint in the body which means it is capable of some pretty amazing and complex movements but because of this it is also one of the areas that is most commonly injured. And from experience having multiple shoulder dislocations and a grade 3 AC joint tear, I know that to be quite true! ----------------------------------A lot of shoulder injuries stem from the shoulder being too tight among other things. Hanging from a bar is a simple but very effective mobility exercise that I like to add into my client's training to help promote shoulder health, allow us to improve over head strength and stability and is also a great grip strengthening exercise. ---------------------------------- Simply grab hold of a chin up bar or anything else that is high enough and can support your body weight and allow your shoulders to relax and stretch out. Ideally doing several sets holding for 30 seconds or more to allow time for the muscle to stretch and create lasting change. The longer you hold the more grip strength endurance you will obviously need which will come in hand when the time comes to do chin ups. ---------------------------------- Like the squat mobility, practicing hanging for a few minutes everyday will help you create lasting change, allow you maintain that change you make and go a long way in helping prevent injuries. Because injuries suck!

"We see 300 homeless men a day..." "We are currently supporting 6 women in our refuge..." "We will take as many care packs as you can offer us, we will never have enough." We have once again started distributing our care pack to women's refuges and homeless shelters and are being reminded of just how significant our homeless crisis is both in the CBD as well as metropolitan and regional areas.  Next week we will be hosting a packing day at Polycom in both Sydney and Melbourne where we hope to be able to make another 300 care packs ready for distribution.  As we always do, we would like to take this opportunity to thank the incredible individuals and organisations that have recently supported us;  We received a cash donation from our good friends at the Flight Centre in Forestville. For those that don't know, Sue and her team have been incredible supporter of ELBH and a drop off location for more than 2 years and we are incredibly grateful for your ongoing support and generosity.  Also thanks to Rio who is a year 9 student. Rio has been busy volunteering his time to pack care packs 💛  We also wish to thank the following for their product donations over the last 2 weeks - you sure have kept us busy, which is exactly the way we like it!!; Keisha & Zarah Meredith Pallister Sarah Crisp Margot and Sarah Claudia and the team at UXC Siemens Chartered Accountants Aust Carnival Cruises Adrian Booth American Express Business Travel Finn Blake Colleen Yuen  Naomi G Harvest Journeys  Thank you to each and every one of you who have supported us via our branches in Syd, Melb and Bris - Every Little Bit Helps

New York you had it last year and it sold out in five days.  Well, now Los Angeles is getting the Museum of Ice Cream and its going to be 4x bigger than the one in #nyc and tickets go on sale April 3, 2017 - $29.00 Adults $18.00 for children and seniors.  Forget everything Nietzsche ever said—God is alive and well, and we have the evidence to prove it. And by proof of the existence of God, we obviously mean an opening date (at long last!) for L.A.'s highly anticipated Museum of Ice Cream. Yes, a museum of ICE CREAM.  After an extremely hyped, limited run in New York last summer (30,000 tickets sold out in five days) the Museum of Ice Cream will be making its way to Los Angeles this April. This is their second location.  The Museum of Ice Cream, according to our sister site Gothamist in New York, "is a museum only in the loosest sense of the word." Think of it more like an eminently Instagrammable, real life Willy Wonka dreamscape of ice cream-themed art and spectacle. The L.A. location will be FOUR times larger than the New York City incarnation (sorry Rotten Apple, but West Coast is the best coast) and will have 10 completely reimagined installations.  Tickets go on sale April 3 at 9 a.m. PST for the general public.  Your links:  http://laist.com/2017/03/28/the_forthcoming_la_museum_of_ice_cr.php#photo-21  M.o I.C. : ://www.museumoficecream.com

Today I had a Body Composition Analysis completed! This is my second scan, and it's kind of a half way scan for me. I am planning on completing another BCA towards the end of the year to check my muscle gain and progress!  Between these 2 photos; - 111kgs to 89kgs, that's a loss of 22kgs! - Body Fat Percentage has gone from 59.8% to 36.7%! That's a total BFP loss of 23.1%! - BMI has gone from 37.1 (obese) to 29.2 (overweight)! That's a total BMI loss of 7.9! - My Visceral Fat level is currently 16, this level should be between 1-9, I still have to work on this number! I can't imagine what level it was at when I was 111kgs 😳  When I completed my first BCA just under 2 years ago, I was told that if I did not change my lifestyle within the next 2 years, I would die at a very young age. I was 59.8% fat, and I had severe Visceral Fat (fat around your organs). I ignored this information for about a year, until finally 2016 rolled around and I realised I was very sick, I was very sore, and I was extremely scared. I decided enough was enough and I changed my life for me. I want to live a long and healthy life, I want to grow old with someone and create a family with someone. I want to be healthy enough to travel, go on adventures and keep up with my future kids. I want to feel healthy and happy within myself! I want to be stronger! I'm slowly battling through each and every day to become the best version of myself! 💪🏻❤🐺 #love #happy #wicca #moonchild #spiritual #dedication #mentality #motivation #inspiration #fit #fitness #fitgirl #weights #gym #progress #weightloss #australia #sydney #worldgympenrith #booty #bulking #gains #squat #health #healthy #strong #lifestyle

A wild night with wildlife !! Wild Camping is a great way to experience the Australian bush & see native animals . Camping in the wild is often the most attractive option, many of the most gorgeous places in the world are thankfully far from five stars hotels . You need wild camping if you want to spend the night gazing stars & seeing wild animals . For many people the thought of wild camping is daunting , you may worry about trouble in the middle of the night from animals or hear an ant fart in the night 😂😂😂 , if you are like this , camp with some experience campers or just give it time .  These types of fears are natural just build up your confidence slowly & dont get discouraged, these types of fears are natural , the more you camp out the more you ll realise how safe wild camping is. Sydney's upper north shore is not your usual first choice to go out for a good dinner, but @brasserielentrecote is a great new addition. In the building in Pymble that housed various restaurants over the last decade, it now breathes the atmosphere of a Parisian bistro. With traditional French fare. The Steak Frites is truly superb, a trimmed 120 days aged Grain Fed Angus MBS 5+ beef, very tender. Delicious with the hand cut chips. According to Bo the best steak he ever had. Steak tartare great too, and so was the raspberry soufflé with wild berry gelato. Good wine list as well. I had a 2011 La Gardine Grenache-Syrah Chateauneuf du Pape, which matched perfectly with the beef. Also a very special father son get together, which has become an annual tradition.

- 小文章第五篇  時光飛逝，來到澳大利亞兩百多個日子。當初承諾自己來到一個沒有人認識的地方開始生活，這個理由簡單也充足。 - 搭電車與各個國家的人一同奔跑趕車、擠沙丁魚上下班。 - 下班到coles wws aldi  假日到market逛逛並採買自己想料理的食材。 - 上班認識到很多國家的人，有些人很nice很喜歡聊天這也是練習英文的機會、有些人還會說一些中文讓你覺得不可思議、有些人即使表現出我不喜歡你但我們還是一起工作。 - 他們的態度值得我學習，不要把自己逼的太緊，休息也是工作的一部分。Slowly ! No快 No快！ 我非常喜歡和他們一起工作，即便我討厭工作，但能和他們聊天、打招呼並漸漸有默契，或許這是我繼續留在這的動力。 - 每週日都會逼自己找個理由出門，到想去的地方走走。也因為如此讓我遇見無預期的驚喜！ 「漸漸的，城市的日常也變成了我的日常。」 - 來到不同的世界後，從小到大認知的價值觀念與思想會不停的衝撞。我不斷思考什麼樣的生活態度才是自己想要也適合自己。 - 「世界很大」這句話早已被講爛了，但真正能定義這句話的內涵只有自己。 「與其說世界很大，不如說你自己能夠決定這個世界有多麼大。」 - 很想說些什麼去重傷我覺得很不可理喻的想法與觀點，但我沒這麼做。 「因為你能決定自己要過怎麼樣的人生。」 現在的我依然在工作，但我不停的在計畫自己的旅程。 「去看我想看到的世界。」

I have had such a lovely day in Sydney today as the weather has been beautiful. ✨🌊 I realised today that I have been in Sydney for nearly 3 months and I had never ventured to North Sydney - that is now ticked off my list ✔️ and the Olympic Pool literally has THE most amazing view of the bridge 🙌 After today I decided to treat myself and make my Pumpkin Macadamia Bread so here ya go beautiful people💕  Ingredients you’ll need: 270g wholewheat flour (OR gluten free flour) 1/2 tsp allspice 1/4 tsp ground cloves 1 tsp ground cinnamon 1/2 tsp ground ginger pinch of salt 1/4 cup macadamia 1/4 dried cranberries 1/4 desiccated coconut 1/2 tsp baking powder 1 tsp baking soda 3/4 cup coconut sugar/brown sugar  1 cup pumpkin puree 2 tbs brown rice syrup/maple syrup 1 mashed banana  Now you’re ready…  Preheat yo’ oven to 175 degrees (fan oven) and grease yo’ bread tin.  Mix all your dry ingredients together in a large mixing bowl EXCEPT the dried cranberries and macadamia nuts.  Then mix together the wet ingredients in your food processor. Once your wet ingredients add in everything in your mixing bowl and slowly pulse the wet and dry together!  After it is well combined mix in the cranberries and macadamia nuts in to the mixture by hand!  Pour it pon yo’ tin den slam it pon de oven for 45-50 minutes.  Give it a cheeky poke with a toothpick and if it comes out clean then start getting hungry because once its cooled… its time for food. #Sydney, capital of New South Wales and one of Australia's largest cities, is best known for its harbourfront Sydney Opera House, with a distinctive sail-like design. Massive Darling Harbour and the smaller Circular Quay port are hubs of waterside life, with the arched Harbour Bridge and esteemed Royal Botanic Garden nearby. Sydney Tower’s outdoor platform, the Skywalk, offers 360-degree views of the city and suburbs. Sydney Aquarium, Taronga Zoo and Wildlife Sydney Zoo shelter animals like koalas, kangaroos, sharks and snakes. Pyrmont’s Sydney Fish Market has a working seafood auction and restaurants serving the day’s catch. There are multicultural dining opportunities all over the city, including in Haymarket’s Chinatown and the restaurants serving the Italian community in Leichhardt. A ferry ride through the harbour is part of the experience in visiting outer Sydney destinations such as Bondi and Manly Beaches – both popular for surfing. - Perth, capital of Western Australia, sits where the Swan River meets the southwest coast. Sandy beaches line its suburbs, and the huge, riverside Kings Park and Botanic Garden on Mt. Eliza offer sweeping views of the city. The Perth Cultural Centre houses the state ballet and opera companies, and occupies its own central precinct, including a theatre, art galleries and the Western Australian Museum. Central Perth also has the interactive Scitech science centre, Perth Mint’s displays of gold bars and nuggets, and Barrack Square’s glass Bell Tower, with its own viewing platform. Shopping is concentrated in pedestrianised Murray and Hay streets, with high-end boutiques on King Street. The neighbouring 19th-century port of Fremantle draws visitors to its craft markets, an 1850s prison and seafood restaurants in the Fishing Boat Harbour. The shoreline north of Perth is known as the Sunset Coast. It's home to family-friendly Cottesloe Beach, popular snorkelling site Marmion Marine Park and Trigg Beach, with large waves for surfing.

Cardio/running gets a lot of shit from the fitness and weight lifting industry. People say it's pointless or unnecessary for fat loss or body goals. Whilst that may be true in some situations, I also believe that if you enjoy cardio then you should do it. I absolutely love going on a run once a week - it's my 'me' time and I don't really care if I might 'lose my gains' so to speak. I know a lot of people literally hate running and if that's you then don't do it but for me it's therapeutic. It's natural for people to get excited when they learn about my freelance life and my predominantly remote working lifestyle. ❤ Yes, it's great to be able to work from anywhere, it's allowed me to travel overseas without sacrificing on my work. But a lot of people also end up saying how it would be great to "stop working for the man" and how they're so over whatever it is they're doing and that the 9 to 5 mediocre life is shit. The thing is, I will never say that to anyone. 😊 My lifestyle isn't for everyone - obviously I only post the fun things, but behind it all... I'm exhausted. I'm chasing every single day. My brain doesn't stop ticking. I've lost so much sleep. I've doubted my abilities. I'm ALWAYS scared about new things I have to do - but I do them because I just have to. I've been close to "giving up" at least once a month only to realise that I'm curious to see what else happens. At the same time, yes - I am free and happy. But like I said, it's not for everyone. The 9 to 5 at least has the stability and you won't have sleepless nights worrying about more things. You've got an expected income. Who knows? Maybe one day I'll end up back in some fulltime job. Maybe I won't. WHO KNOWS. 😂 If your 9 to 5 is shit, then do something about it. Make it better for yourself, but don't just complain and keep on living that way. And if you do want to be your own boss, then start working towards it - just remember that even if I'm my own boss, I have many clients that I have to keep happy so it's not that different. The reason I live and work the way I do is because I love searching for happiness and other ways of living, while making the most of every situation. Ok, the flexibility of being able to travel is great - but even I have to stay put in one place at a time to work. It's just doing what you gotta do to get what you want. 🙏🏻 • • • • • #digitalnomad#freelancer#freelancelife#workfromanywhere#workfromhome#workremotely#workandtravel#behindthescenes#workhard#confession#travel#travelgram#chaseyourdreams#happiness#reallife#coogee#sydney#australia#ocean#dowhatyoulove#lifeisshort#namaste#liveunconventionally#waves#nature

Refuelling from this morning's yoga class while admiring my beautiful tan by @catherinelizbethmua ☀️ Confession time: After filming last week's video about cereals I sat down and ate a big bowl of those Milo 'protein clusters' 🙈 I grew up eating Milo cereal every morning for breakfast and I just wanted to relive some of those memories 😂 While it was pretty darn delicious, it also reminded me of why I don't eat that stuff anymore - it is SO addictive! Not only did I want to go back for second and third helpings, but I'm still craving it 5 days later 🤦🏼‍♀️ We often hear about calories, but it's also important to think about food in terms of how it affects our bodies 👉🏼 Ask yourself: Does eating a particular food keep me feeling full and energetic for hours after, or does it leave me craving other sweet foods and wishing I could eat more? 🍶 There is nothing wrong with cereal per se, it's the added sugars that come with processed cereals that I tell my clients to avoid 🙅🏼 These days I make my own cereal - that way, I know exactly what ingredients I'm putting into my bowl and the affect it's going to have on my body 👍🏼 It doesn't even take any longer than eating packaged cereal would, I just put a few spoonfuls of various ingredients into my bowl and away I go 💃🏼 I generally use rolled oats as my base, and top it with a spoonful each of slivered almonds, sunflower seeds, pepitas and flaxseeds 🥄 Then, for flavour I'll add either half a grated apple, a handful of berries or half a cup of my homemade fruit compote 🍓Finally, I top it with either some milk (or milk alternative) or a big dollop of Greek yoghurt and of course, a sprinkle of cinnamon ⭐️ This type of cereal really will keep you full for a long time because it's loaded with complex carbs, protein and healthy fats 👌🏼 The only sugar that it contains is natural sugar in the form of fruit which is a) nowhere near as addictive as processed sugar and b) enters the bloodstream at a much slower pace, thanks to the fibre that comes with it, so you won't experience that crazy blood-sugar rise then sudden drop 📈 I think it's time to get off this sunny step and begin my day! Happy Thursday everyone 🙋🏼

Isn't life crazy? 8 yrs ago this month, I was watching my whirlwind romance gasp its last breath. And I was watching my job do much the same.  7 yrs ago to the month, I was re-building a sense of home for the second time in six months, on the other side of the world away from all that I called familiar. I was having panic attacks in the street and weeping fits behind closed doors.  All of it led to the beginning of my beginning. Since then I've learned to roll with the lives and deaths within my own life better, watching chapters and doors open and close. And don't get me wrong, the transitions can still hurt like all hell but I'm learning.  Now? Now I understand that there are a few important priorities when it comes to change.  1. It is all too easy to identify the loss/ the thing falling away as part of you. It's not. It's part of your life but not part of you. You are just as whole and as complete and safe as you always have been.  2. When it comes to the final retrospective, it will be far more important how you handled things than what the things actually were. Your sense of self, strength, grace, compassion, growth isn't measured by the things that happen to/for you but how you navigate through them. And that includes being wise enough to ask for help when needed.  3. Assigning blame or sitting in shame is the quickest way of avoiding the learning available. Fixing your gaze on 'shoulda, woulda, coulda' lifts you right out of the present moment and all you can gain from it.  4. Don't mistake solitude for stillness. We all need quiet periods to absorb, digest and integrate the changes, especially introverts. But fear of the unknown can keep us there longer than actually supports us. Where possible, stick to some kind of routine that keeps you in the world just a little.  5. It's necessary to feel. That which we dampen biochemically nestles into our body and sets up home there. And that which we suppress entirely suppresses its happy counterpart too. Find someone or somewhere that allows you to safely work through the spectrum so that you don't carry the trauma with you.  Change is the only constant in our lives so befriend it as much as you can.

I'm nervous to post this as it's a bit of a mind blurt from when I woke up this morning but here goes...some creative writing from me...😰..... "Maybe hell is disguised as a paradise with all the things that you could ever ask for. Then slowly but surely and painfully all those things get taken from you one by one until you are standing there left bare with only yourself that must help you to rise again into whatever the reality of what a true Utopia would look like. Soul bare and heart open we must climb back up to find our own inner peace of mind again, climbing away from the downward spiralling heartache and awful gut feelings we didn't listen to as we reached for something that was perhaps not meant for us or that we ignored when we should have taken note.  We live with such masks on these days I think it's so hard to tell fact from fiction. That we begin even fooling ourselves. A simple life can bring us down but in reality up; to view all the things we missed but we must walk through some of the painful honest truths of that climb down first. Like an Escher staircase it's hard to know what is up and what is down.  We are magical creatures that don't even understand just how magical we truly are without all the bells and whistles. Just us, naked, stripped of robes, glistening in all our glory as we become real with ourselves, we shall find peace again on earth. Nothing we buy, sell, or do to serve our ego can ever fill us to the point of contentment. The modern world has vibrationally slowed that I can sometimes almost hear her screeching and moaning to a premature halt.  I'm not religious, I was never brought up that way, but believe perhaps the many words and scripts are metaphors for what we go through as people. So that only things are revealed to those that are ready and willing when the timing is right. Or the specific lesson that is needed comes forward in an obvious fashion so we can better grasp it with our own free will & decisiveness.  I hope I find my feet again once more." -  Jacqueline Freestone xx 😘  Lots of love ❤️ #words #thoughts #writing #australia #sydney #deepthinking #love #spirituality #portraitphotography #model #imeannooffense

The Swilhouse Group who own this bar have several awesome venues also worth taking note of such as Shady Pines, Restaurant Hubert and Frankies Pizza by the slice. They wanted to call their first bar Swillhouse but the Sydney licensing police thought that would make people want to drink too much. That bar, Shady Pines, is a prohibition style bar with no signage on the street. The only sign was their license that said the licensee was Swillhouse! It's not summer anymore in Sydney. Less time spent on the beach = less motivation to stay in shape.  Don't worry, I feel the same way too. When the pressure to look good isn't as high, we tend to fall off the band wagon every now and again.  So how do we combat this?  Here's what I did... 1. Set myself a goal (110kg clean & Jerk/80kg snatch) 2. Gave myself a timeline (1st November - hold yourself accountable) 3. Put a plan together (hire someone to help) 4. Make sure you want it enough! (Don't do something you think you want, make sure you're doing it for the right reasons or it just won't stick). 5. Enjoy it!  Try it out... No matter what time of year it is. If you set yourself a target, motivation will follow.

7/10 - @Fuel Espresso Brookvale – Bacon and egg roll - $8 . "My shin's name is Hackett, can you Grant my wish and smash a record on my jacket" – I discovered this - what I can only assume is a drunken freestyle - while waiting for a bacon and egg roll from Fuel Espresso.  Needless to say it was after a particularly loose night and I was rougher than 20 grit sandpaper. Do you ever hunch over your food like Gollum so 1. You don’t make eye contact with anyone you know, and 2. No one can steal your precioussss? I do... and I did.  I chuckled to myself as I tucked into this smoked bacon, egg, rocket, tomato relish and aioli on a long Italian roll *insert wog hand gesture*. The egg was overcooked, but this flavour log hit the flavour G-spot. It was a balanced roll, the Campos had gusto and the combination of both soothed the dust.  Note – When at Fuel Espresso always request a freshly made B&E, pre-made B&Es are for pussies. Furthermore, live a little and give a fake name, only pussies give their real name when ordering a coffee. Yours sincerely, not Jim xo #🐷🍳

2017 Youth Summit done and dusted!  The focus was on youth transitions into employment. We recognise that young people from newly-arrived backgrounds often find it challenging to secure their first job and gain local work experience. Therefore, the Youth Summit engaged the youth on the topics of work experience, interning, traineeships and volunteering as a pathway to paid employment.  Everyone was also treated to some Darcy St Project coffee and hot chocolates too.  I wanted to thank Rohullah from ADSi (Auburn Diversity Services Inc) for inviting us as a guest speaker, workshop facilitator and being part of a wonderful community of organisations for the day.  #adsi #ascon #dooleys #headspace #cmrc #pcyc #liverpoolmrc #ssi #navitas #andsome #darcystproject #socialenterprise #coffeeschool #brewbar #community #socent #auburn #pcyc #sydney #australia #youthsummit2017 #coffee #cafe #specialtycoffee #espresso #youth #employment #jobs #kickinggoals

We set the proposal up in the park where he first asked her to be his girlfriend. At the first sign of sunset he took her hand and walked down the candle lit path we prepared. Once they arrived to the location filled with her favourite fairy lights, he handed her a letter. As she finished reading he got down on one knee and asked "Will you marry me?". They celebrate with a glass of champagne as they wait for their limousine to take them to the next location we planned - A 12 course fine dining experience.

TBT: Diamond in You - No. 1 2010 (Tatsuo Mijayajima: Connect With Everything 2017, MCA)  Stemming from the Buddhist concept of 'kongochi', it is preached that kongo, meaning 'diamond', cannot be acquired from outside but every human has this within. The LED tickers and unfolding mirrors of stainless steel symbolise this 'inner diamond' and, excluding zero which relates to stagnation and death, the numbers emphasise infinite time. Guy Lambton Menzies, aviator born in #Drummoyne, Sydney, on the 7th January 1931, and is best known for being the first aviator to fly solo from Australia to NZ, in 11 hours 45 minutes. . The period between World War I and World War II is often referred to as the Golden Age of Aviation, and was notable for many 'firsts'. In Drummoyne, Guy Menzies had learnt to fly in his teenage years, and at 21 years of age was determined to leave his mark in the record books. . The first crossing of the Tasman by air had been achieved in September 1928 by Charles Kingsford Smith and Charles Ulm in the Southern Cross. Menzies had purchased the Avro Sports Avian that Smith had flown from England to Australia, the "Southern Cross Junior", then considered one of the best small aircraft available. Even so, flying across the Tasman was a risky venture. . Anticipating that he would be denied permission for the flight, Menzies informed the authorities and his family that he was flying to Perth... then headed off in the opposite direction. He left Sydney at 1 am on 7 January 1931, and headed for Blenheim on the north east of NZ's South Island. The flight was dogged by bad weather and for much of the flight Menzies was flying blind. He was driven way off course and the flight ended in a crash landing, with the plane upside down in the La Fontaine Swamp near Hari Hari on the west coast. The flight had taken 11 hours and 45 minutes. . Menzies had secured a place in the record books as the first to fly solo to NZ. . Menzies' return to Sydney was somewhat more sedate, travelling back by sea with  his damaged plane on the SS Maunganui. . Soon after his return, Menzies decided to sell his plane and left for Britain where he joined the Royal Air Force. During World  War II he served as a Squadron Leader and was killed on 1 November 1940, when his flying boat was shot down over Italy. . Today, there is a memorial at Hari Hari commemorating his flight. In Australia, Menzies Reserve in Drummoyne marks his service during the Second War, along with that of his brother, Ian Menzies, who served with the RAAF and also died during combat. . #aviationhistory #history #sydney #canadabay #war #guymenzies

Всем привет! Сегодня я вам расскажу, что можно увидеть и где побывать в Сиднее за бесплатно. 👣 Несчетное количество пляжей, больших и маленьких, спрятанных и известных, с океаном и в заливах. Самый популярный и знаменитый пляж - Бондай бич. 👣 Тропы вдоль побережья с обалденными видами. 👣 Киты видны с некоторых мысов. 👣 Королевский ботанический сад. Про него одно слово - красотища! 👣 Национальные парки. По сути это леса с дикой природой и живностью. 👣 Харбор-Бридж. Мост можно перейти пешком, всего 1км. Виды открываются потрясающие. 👣 Опера Хаус. Можно обойти вокруг, подойти, потрогать, внутрь заглянуть. 👣 Картинная галерея. Здесь есть всё от импрессионизма до современного и аборигенного искусства. Вход свободный на постоянные выставки. 👣 Музей современного искусства. Здесь вы найдёте более 4 тыс работ австралийских художников. Вход свободный на постоянные выставки. 👣 Выставка Белый Кролик. Здесь собраны самые крупные коллекции современного китайского искусства в мире. 👣 Музей географических открытий в районе Рокс. Здесь собраны тысячи лет истории. 👣 Австралийский национальный морской/судоходный музей. Здесь бесплатны некоторые части музея. 👟👟 В общем, ходить не переходить в Сиднее, красивых мест очень много. BRAIN GAINS!!! 💪🎓 . [self awareness] . In a society where we have so many constant distractions 🔊🎊📺📱💻🌋🎪and so much noise🗣 we tend to lose SELF AWARENESS which can also be referred to as MINDFULLNESS. This can lead to a distorted perspective and unneeded stress 🙇‍♀️🙇🏻 . Meditation🙏 has gained a lot of traction it seems recently. I myself have began a practice albeit not as consistent as I would like but working on it . Everything in our body adapts to the stimulus we give it. From our muscles to our tendons, to even our brains. An approach life such as seeking constant growth and improvement will give you just that over time 📆🗓 . A simple meditation exercise: 1️⃣Sit in a comfortable position without distractions 2️⃣close your eyes and take relatively deep and relaxed breaths 3️⃣focus on your breathing. In your mind repeat "breathe in", "breathe out" slowly as you breathe. If you get distracted just return to the breathe . Let's get those FOCUS 💪 muscles jacked 😏 . Comment below 📝⬇️and let me know what you guys think about meditation and your own experiences if you have tried it 🙏👍 . #meditation #relaxation #selfawareness #peaceful #mentalcalm #antichaos #mindfullness

Head games

🇦🇺🥂✨❤️ Um ano no país desconhecido que hoje se tornou nossa casa, onde nos descobrimos a cada dia, onde vemos nos mesmo de uma forma diferente. Nesse um ano vivemos tantas coisas boas, alguns momentos tensos tbm é clarooo, como o tal do inglês, olha mais esse inglês da o que falar viu... Aquela saudade dos familiares e amigos que dói e não é pouco viu "/ mas nada como uma boa dose de choro pra colocar tudo pra fora e lavar a alma e começar tudo de novo. O tempo rei dos reis tem se encarregado de fazer com que a saudade venha, mas de uma forma mais familiar um sentimento que fará parte das nossas vidas enquanto nossa escolha for ficar aqui. Em meio tanta bagunça de sentimentos há muita alegria, felicidade e Paz. Descobertas então, são inúmeras e os micos já pagos? só Deus na causa hahah!!! E as entrevistas de emprego com um inglês mais que sem vergonha "ABAFA" o frio na barriga é demais e parece nunca ter fim... Os amigos que são família não tem preço, os simples finais de semanas cheios de histórias e risadas é bom demais. O melhor de tudo é saber que temos um ao outro, dividir tudo isso com vc é simplesmente incrível e impagável!!! Que seja assim até quando Deus quiser. Eu cuido de você e você cuida de mim.  Hoje sem sombra de dúvidas e com toda a certeza do mundo fizemos a escolha certa!! E o sentimento que invade e transborda é a gratidão, como sou grata por tudo vivido até agora. E que venha mais dias, mais histórias, mais desafios, mais risadas, mais tudo o que há de melhor nessa Austrália de aí meu Deuuuusss!!! #aussie #sydney #cheers #love

. 🤓💀📚ANATOMY FRIDAY 📚💀🤓. . RULES 👉🏽 You have to answer straight away, without looking up the answer! . It's important to understand that the 'Rotator Cuff' isn't one muscle! It's four seperate muscles, each with two major roles . 1. Cuff the head of the humerus from the anterior, lateral and posterior sides, into the glenohumeral cavity. This is imperative to the stability of the shoulder joint from all angles . 2. Each muscle has a different role to play in internal rotation, external rotation and the first 30deg of abduction too. It's very important to know which muscles is responsible for each muscle when looking at functional anatomy and training  the appropriate muscles for your client . #anatomyfridays #fitcollege #fitness #education #exercise #science #anatomy #teamgws #gws #sydney #west #castlehill #muscles #rotatorcuff

Today is #worldhealthday and early colonial health is something that is very close to home for National Trust Australia (NSW) staff! The building we occupy was originally constructed in 1815 by Governor Macquarie and designed by Lieutenant John Watts, as a military hospital. The hospital was built on Observatory Hill to take advantage of the fresh sea breeze and because it was close to military barracks in present day #Wynyard. When the barracks at Wynyard were moved to Paddington the military hospital became redundant as new facilities were available at the Victoria Barracks. 📷: @statelibrarynsw  #nationaltrustnsw #nswhistory #colonialhistory #colonialhealth #nationaltrustcentre #militarybarracks #sydneyhistory #healthhistory #history #sydney #australianheritage #australianhistory

This consisted of the Minerva Theatre (now the Metro Theatre), The Minerva Cafe and Nightclub. The building was designed by C. Bruce Dellit in 1937, with building completed in 1939. It's the first time I'm going camping and even though a tent is not the most comfortable place to sleep, believe me guys the view in the morning is worth everything. It's getting cold and night falls fast here at this time of year. Days are short especially since it's advised not to drive at night because of wild animals. So far we've made it to a free camp near the river. Feel free to follow my instagram stories to see more 😊

❤️Sagrado Coração de Jesus🙏! ✍️O coração que ama sente profundamente o amor de Jesus doado na cruz, capaz de salvar toda a humanidade do pecado. Tenhamos um coração grande para amar, perdoar e, com fidelidade, seguir o Senhor na missão. ☝️O justo sabe que Deus está ao seu lado e lhe dá forças para resistir às incompreensões e para realizar obras que deem testemunho de fidelidade ao Pai. 🙌📖 Evangelho (Jo 10,31-42) — O Senhor esteja convosco. — Ele está no meio de nós. 🙌 — Proclamação do Evangelho de Jesus Cristo + segundo João. — Glória a vós, Senhor. 🕯 Naquele tempo, 31os judeus pegaram pedras para apedrejar Jesus. 32E ele lhes disse: “Por ordem do Pai, mostrei-vos muitas obras boas. Por qual delas me quereis apedrejar?” 33Os judeus responderam: “Não queremos te apedrejar por causa das obras boas, mas por causa de blasfêmia, porque sendo apenas um homem, tu te fazes Deus!” 34Jesus disse: “Acaso não está escrito na vossa Lei: ‘Eu disse: vós sois deuses’? 35Ora, ninguém pode anular a Escritura: se a Lei chama deuses as pessoas às quais se dirigiu a palavra de Deus, 36por que então me acusais de blasfêmia, quando eu digo que sou Filho de Deus, eu a quem o Pai consagrou e enviou ao mundo? 37Se não faço as obras do meu Pai, não acrediteis em mim. 38Mas, se eu as faço, mesmo que não queirais acreditar em mim, acreditai nas minhas obras, para que saibais e reconheçais que o Pai está em mim e eu no Pai”. 39Outra vez procuravam prender Jesus, mas ele escapou das mãos deles. 40Jesus passou para o outro lado do Jordão, e foi para o lugar onde, antes, João tinha batizado. E permaneceu ali. 41Muitos foram ter com ele, e diziam: “João não realizou nenhum sinal, mas tudo o que ele disse a respeito deste homem, é verdade”. 42E muitos, ali, acreditaram nele.📖🙌 — Palavra da Salvação. — Glória a vós, Senhor.🙏 #saojoaobatistadelasalle #santaursulina #mariapassanafrente rogai por nós 🙌⛪🇧🇷🕊💒🌍👨‍👩‍👧‍👦📖🙏#liturgiacancaonova#newyork#paris#roma#madri#barcelona#saopaulo#lisboa#usa#atenas#buenosaires#santiago#sydney#cingapura#instambul#losangeles#luanda#berlim#londres#jerusalem#viena#hongkong#dublin#espanha#argentina#suiça

Giờ thì cứ ngẩng lên cái là 1g sáng : (((. Thở 1 cái là tới tối. Lên giường ngủ thẳng cẳng và sáng mở mắt thì cong mông chạy.  Mà cũng tốt. Ít nhất giờ thì b mình cần làm gì. Mình muốn gì. Cũng chẳng có tgian mà nghĩ tới những thứ cũ rích nhảm nhí. Cũng chẳng còn đặt nặng nhưng sự quan tâm hời hợt. Có những ng thật kì lạ. Mình k yêu cầu họ quan tâm nhưng họ vẫn đôi lúc quăng vào mặt mình 1 câu hỏi. Và r thì k cần b câu trlời là cái khỉ mốc gì : )). Như cho có vậy đấy. 1 kiểu bố thí sự quan tâm? Anw: tự dưng hơi ngộp vì n thứ ập tới 1 lúc nên bán than tí. Chứ có tiền là vẫn vui : )). Here's a question I get often:⠀ ⠀ "How much time does it take to run your R+F business?"⠀ ⠀ ⏱To make a Facebook post? ~3 minutes ⠀ ⏱To respond to a message? ~3 minutes⠀ ⏱To send a message? ~3 minutes⠀ ⏱To have a conversation? ~15 minutes⠀ ⏱To train a team? ~10-30 minutes⠀ ⏱To have coffee with a friend? ~40 minutes⠀ ⏱To listen to a training call? ~25 minutes⠀ ⠀ To make deliveries? (we don’t make deliveries)⠀ To sell inventory? (we don’t carry inventory)⠀ To throw parties? (no parties required, unless we want to)⠀ To place an order? (our customers order from our websites)⠀ ⠀ This is something that fits in and around your life from wherever and whenever you choose.  Making TIME now to change what your entire future looks like is TOTALLY WORTH IT!  Bottom line, on an average day, I run my business successfully in 30 minutes to an hour.  Leaving time to be with the kids, help with homework, park time. Now THAT feels like time freedom to me. "I was a boot maker and then a tram driver. Do you know Bennelong Point? That was a tram depot. I worked the last shift before it was torn down to become the Sydney Opera House. . I drove the trams all over Sydney before they were taken away. There was a passenger called Bea Miles, and she called swear like a trooper! She never paid a penny for her ride. She would just tell the inspectors to get stuffed. Everybody knew of her. The whole time I was on the trams I never saw Bea pay the fare. Isn't that funny? . I've been in Waterloo for many decades. My wife, Vivian, and I had a great life together. It would have been 60 years this year... There's not a day that goes by when I don't think about her. Стою сегодня на перекрестке, жду, когда мне  зеленая стрелка загорится, а сбоку подъезжает старенький ягуар с меховыми сиденьями и огромными музыкальными колонками сзади. В машине сидит лысый мужик и тётенька. Оба в темных очках и жуют жвачку, как два верблюда. Им около сорока, но понты никто не отменял😄 #атемвременемвавстралии мы говорим о вождении. Как я получала права тут я уже писала в одном из своих постов. В июне будет год как я езжу. И все больше и больше этому радуюсь . Без машины в Сиднее тяжеловато. Поехать туда, поехать сюда, отвезти ребёнка на кружки, съездить на пляж. Конечно, мы пол года жили тут без машины и ничего, но были весьма ограничены в выборе развлечений и путешествий. На поезде/автобусе дороговато выходит на троих, не так удобно и не во все места можно добраться.  Маршруток как в России тут нет. Такси стоит бешено. На дорогах народ в основном спокойный, дружелюбный и законопослушный. Конечно, тут такие штрафы, что можно разориться, если часто нарушать. Плюс снимают баллы и могут отнять права. И потом хоть кадриль перед полицией  пляши, фиг они тебе их вернут. У кого full drive license можно выпивать бокальчик вина или бутылочку пива. По пятницам и выходным на дорогах стоят полицейские и просят дунуть в трубочку. Один знакомый так дунул, что на долго лишился прав. Права уже вернул, а гражданство получить не может, потому что его внесли в черный список злостных нарушителей. Так что миру мир, а дорогам вежливых и умных водителей. Если хотите узнать больше о получении/смене прав в Австралии, об особенностях местного вождения и в какую копеечку обходится тут содержание машины, заходите по тэгу #атемвременемвавстралии и ни в чем себе не отказывайте😄 #австралия#сидней #australia #sydney #русскиевавстралии

The evolution of H.E.L.P transpired with a tribe mentality - friends, family + strangers coming together to create something beautifully authentic + profound.  As we approach the end of the first week open in Sydney AUS and the start of our first week open in Los Angeles USA. We are humbled + full of gratitude to those that have H.E.L.Ped us along the way + continue to support us each + every step. …it all started with a profound sense of wrong…that needed to be set right. We all needed H.E.L.P... “The grand scheme of a life, maybe (just maybe), is not about knowing or not knowing, choosing or not choosing. Perhaps what is truly known can’t be described or articulated by creativity or logic, science or art — but perhaps it can be described by the most authentic and meaningful combination of the two: poetry: As Robert Frost wrote, a poem 'begins as a lump in the throat, a sense of wrong, a homesickness, a lovesickness. It is never a thought to begin with.' I recommend the following course of action for those who are just beginning their careers or for those like me, who may be reconfiguring midway through: heed the words of Robert Frost. Start with a big, fat lump in your throat, start with a profound sense of wrong, a deep homesickness, or a crazy lovesickness, and run with it.” ― Debbie Millman #humanevolutionlifestyleproject #sydney #losangeles #helpcircles 📸 @emilyobrien_photography

"Have you considered maintenance and renovation costs?" A larger property comes with highers costs for maintenance, property taxes, utilities and insurance. It's important to factor in these expenses before you decide on the right property. Another consideration is whether or not you'll need to renovate to make it your ideal home.  An attractive alternative to moving is renovating or extending your existing home. You can do this by accessing the equity in your existing home or extending your loan which may work out cheaper. Ensure you don't overextend on capitalising which means spending more on renovations than the return you'll get.  Working with an experienced agent can help you make the right decision. A company has many levels of communication--from management to employees, between departments, between management groups and between individual employees. To maintain morale, communication lines need to remain open and important information needs to be delivered in a timely fashion. For example, if a small number of layoffs are being planned, then it is important to communicate the magnitude of the layoffs to employees so that rumors do not get spread that could shatter morale. Laying off employees usually has a negative impact on morale, but allowing employees that are not scheduled to be laid off to believe that they could damage morale even further. . . An Indian Head massage is the ideal way to get a person “out of their head”, far far away from everyday emotional and mental stress. 💆🏻The massage usually goes between 25 – 45 minutes, and may or may not use certain oils in the hair and on the body. Starting at the upper back, the Indian Head masseuse begins by applying pressure to points that dissolve knots and relax the muscles. They then move to the shoulders and upper arms to release other common areas of tension, and to the neck and head to release headache-causing blockages and to encourage better circulation of the cerebral fluid. The massage then progresses to the scalp, relaxing the entire head, encouraging circulation and stimulating hair growth. Lastly a gentle face massage that may relieve symptoms of sinusitis & headaches, and encourages good circulation and a glowing complexion. Don't forget to swipe left 🙋🏻 #sydney #headmassage #relaxationstation #massage #therapy #sydney #essentialoils

영어를 잘 활용하고 싶다면 단순히 읽고 듣고 쓰고 말하기를 잘 하려고 노력하기 보다는 영어를 사용하는 민족의 문화적 배경과 언어의 기원들을 습득해 그 언어를 이해, 공감하는 것이 중요하다.  P. 54 외국어를 잘하려면 단지 자기 생각을 표현할 수 있는 단어나 문장을 만드는 능력을 갖추는 것만으로는 부족하다. 그에 못지않게 ‘어떤 상황에서 누구에게 말할 권한이 있는가, 언제 말해야 하고 언제 침묵해야 하는가, 어떤 사람과 이런 말을 해도 되는가, 역할이나 계급이 다른 사람에게 어떤 언어를 써야 하는가, 말과 함께 사용해도 되는 제스처는 무엇인가’ 등등까지 알아야 한다는 것이다. 칼질 할 줄 아는 것과 위대한 셰프가 되는 것은 다르다.  P.167 문장의 요소들을 묶은 나사를 푸는 습관이 바로 분석적 사고며, 분석적 사고를 가진 사람은 영어만 잘하는 것이 아니라, 이런 사고에 기인해서 기술한 여러 철학·인문학·과학책을 원서로 줄줄 읽을 줄 아는 능력도 동시에 생길 것이다.  P. 277  나는 새로운 외국어를 배울 때 굿리즈Goodreads 같은 웹사이트에 들어가서 ‘이탈리아 사람이 쓴 최고의 책 100권’ 등을 검색해서 1권부터 차례로 읽어 내려가는 방식으로 문화 독해력을 길렀다. 무식한 방식이지만 효과는 무척 컸다. 그래서 나는 외국어 공부는 시작하자마자 원서부터 읽는 것이 중요하다고 믿는다.  #플루언트#조승연#북스타그램#책스타그램#독서#sydney#4월8일

Other than that I suppose happiness is just a feeling of ease, a feeling that you want to stay in a moment forever. Have been searching if there is any nice coffee shop ☕️that I can rest from a long walk to Sydney University.🚶🏻‍♀️🌞 I ordered a flat white and a pulled pork bagel. The flat white was great with a scent of acidity and a taste of medium roast. The milk was frothed precisely at it's smoothness and temperature. The bagel was fantastic.😋 The outer layer is crispy yet the inner part which consists of mustard, spinach (I guess?), pulled pork and coleslaw is still cool. As you might feel awkward if the salad in between becomes hot. The graffiti on the wall decorated the dark tone of the inner design. Which gives a key tone to the shop. I especially like the big table with a large vase on it. 😍Staff are nice yet we could not have a longer conversation as they are closing the bar when I have made my order. But everything is lovely. Looking forward to visiting here again. #coffee #coffeeinsydney #flatwhite #bagel #pulledpork #sydneyuniversity #sydney🇦🇺 #sydney

Enjoy this vlog! 😘 ____________________________________________________ Vlog Part 1. @thesmellycheesecake 🌟My thoughts...🤔 This was one wonderful & delicious foodie adventure experience. Thankyou to my workmate & friend @min_jeong__k & the manager at the smelly cheesecake for hooking me up with brunch, coffees, desserts to enjoy & try out 🤔😋👌 You guys really went out of your way for this chubba panda. I was welcomed with a beautifully set table, the manager made me my favourite latte which was absolutely delicious and not too sweet, delicious food which all tasted amazing and felt it was a good amount of food for one serving on each brunch dish, and the manager surprised me with 3 desserts to try 😍 not just one but 3. Well there was a parmasen marscapone one which was very light, slight sweetness everything about this cheese cake was light like a cloud but still had that rich creamy taste and you want to keep eating it. loved it! 😄 the second one i was little hesitant as I have tried this cake before somewhere else but since they brought it out... Well here the Watermelon&cream was fresh & i loved that part of this cake but due to personal taste i cannot get over the floral taste that goes with it. This would be my least favourite cake. But tried it again since it was part of tasting and said YOLO down the hatch lol  It cleanse the pallette for sure, its beautiful, unique and different and to be tried at least once 😄 last cake was an absolute delight fresh short cake with refreshing strawberries, a cake i would devour on my own delish! 😂 im just in a lovely foodcoma after my trip to the smelly cheesecake i was really treated well 😍 I really enjoyed everything. The food, the desserts, the service, the atmosphere. It really was an enjoyable and very tasty foodie experience. Thankyou also to the people who cooked up my brunches, prepared desserts and for the wonderful service. See you guys definitely again!!👌🐼❤ Swipe left to continue to watch the 2nd part of the vlog and swipe again for a slideshow of food i tried at the smelly cheesecake.Enjoy this #Vlog

Let's talk about the history of Polenta! 🌽🇮🇹 The term "polenta" derives from the Latin "puls", a sort of porridge of farro ("far", a Latin cereal of which there exist regional variants) which formed the basic diet of ancient Italic peoples, while the Greeks usually employed barley flour. Before the introduction of maize from the American continent, polenta was made also with other grains such as, in addition to barley and farro, rye, millet, buckwheat and wheat. Some researchers argue that the "puls" was originally a mixture that included legume seeds. To this regard it should be noted that, especially in some regions of Southern Italy, a polenta is still in use made from broad beans accompanied with such vegetables as chicory. The first documented cultivation of maize in Northern Italy dates back to Lovere, in Valcamonica. Gabriele Rosa argues that the cultivation of maize was introduced in Lovere in 1638, for the first time in Italy.  M. Compagnoni attributed the introduction of this crop to Pietro Gajoncelli, who in 1658 imported the first grains of corn from the Americas. What is certain is that, starting from the late 17th century, cornmeal was to surpass chestnut flour in the daily consumption of the inhabitants of Valcamonica. Lino Ertani mentions a report from the parish priest of the village of Darfo, dated July 10, 1741, who wrote: "The village of Darfo consists of 784 souls... of these, most in the morning eat polenta and a good part of them again eat it in the evening." ... to be continued ✨  #polenta #polenteria #polentachips #polenteriabianco #sydneyroyaleastershow #sydneyfood #sydney #corn #farm #myeastershow #foodporn #piaggio #ape #polenteriape #biancokitchen #celiac #glutenfree

Anzac Bridge on a beautiful Sunday morning in Sydney. It's an 8-lane cable-stayed bridge spanning Johnstons Bay between Pyrmont and Glebe Island (close to the CBD). The bridge is 32.2 m (105 ft 8 in) wide and the main span is 345 m (1,132 ft) long. It was opened in 1995 as the Glebe Island Bridge & was renamed the Anzac Bridge on Remembrance Day in 1998.  An Australian Flag flies atop the eastern pylon and a New Zealand Flag flies atop the western pylon. STAMPEDE  The next day the huge crowd that had arrived for the Feast heard that Jesus was entering Jerusalem. They broke off palm branches and went out to meet him.  And they cheered:  Hosanna! Blessed is he who comes in God’s name!  Yes! The King of Israel!  Jesus got a young donkey and rode it, just as the Scripture has it: No fear, Daughter Zion: See how your king comes, riding a donkey’s colt.  The disciples didn’t notice the fulfillment of many Scriptures at the time, but after Jesus was glorified, they remembered that what was written about him matched what was done to him.  The crowd that had been with him when he called Lazarus from the tomb, raising him from the dead, was there giving eyewitness accounts. It was because they had spread the word of this latest God-sign that the crowd swelled to a welcoming parade.  The Pharisees took one look and threw up their hands: “It’s out of control. The world’s in a stampede after him.”

시드니에 와서 가장 많이 들은 말은 단연 "~는 퍼스에 있어요?" 였다. 퍼스를 한번도 와보지 않은 사람, 퍼스에 대해 모르는 사람이 많다는 것을 새삼 느꼈다. 분명 퍼스에 대한 무시가 아닌 모르는것에 대한 호기심이라 생각한다. 어제 간 블루 마운틴에서 동행자분께 퍼스 얘기를 하니 "퍼스가 뭐예요?" 라는 답이 돌아왔다. 내 블로그 혹은 페이스북을 통해서 퍼스 관련 질문들이 들어온다. 하지만, 퍼스에 대해 낯선 사람들이 훨씬 더 많다는 것을 시드니 출장중에 새삼 느끼게 되었다. 퍼스 현지 거주중인 사람으로써, 퍼스가 더 알려지길 바라면서 앞으로는 어떻게 하면 여행자들의 시선을 끌만한 재밌는 여행을 만들어 볼까 고민을 하게된다. ------------------------------------------- 🌴 Facebook.com/wanderlust.heather ✏️ Blog: www.travel-heather.tk 📩 Enquiry: ht.seoge@gmail.com 📍서호주, 퍼스 여행 문의 @from_perth . . #travel #instasnap #travelsnap #traveler #australia #instatravel #follow #followme #sydneylife #sydney #sydneycbd #여행에미치다 #호주 #호주여행 #여행자 #여행 #세계여행 #데일리 #일상 #맞팔 #선팔 #팔로우 #퍼스여행 #퍼스투어 #시드니 #시드니여행 #출장 #호주투어 #호주여행

🇦🇺 呼，忙碌的日子終於有一個小休了。現在來補發二月時去澳洲的感想。 這次去了澳洲的悉尼還有紐卡索。澳洲給我的感覺是一個放大版的香港😂一個空氣清新一點，生活節奏慢一點，還有點不方便的香港。 非常幸運地在十天的旅程(除去了乘飛機的時間其實只有八天)之中只有一天是雨天，其他時候要不是放晴就是有一點陰天。還記得有一晚窗外下着滂沱大雨，我以為明早起來將會是個雨天，怎料是陽光充沛的一天。多虧天公做美，我們才能在澳洲盡興。 記得第一天到澳洲，我們就出發到市區在雪梨港灣大橋附近遊了一圈，尚未適應當地天氣的我們都汗流浹背，完全沒有什麼興奮的心情或是強大購物意欲。晚上在達令港享用完晚膳，拍過照之後便到酒店休息了。經歷了9小時有多的長途飛機，大家都累透了。即使只是剛到悉尼，還沒有緊湊的行程，一到酒店我們都趕著要睡覺。 Ps二月是香港的"冬天" 第二天，我們早上去了動物園參觀樹熊和袋鼠，下午去了藍山遠觀傳說中的三姊妹石，然後將那裡僅有的四項遊樂設施都玩了一遍，森林教育徑也走了一圈。膽小的我也在這裡玩了接近垂直的過山車，嚇死寶寶了ㅠㅠ。有興趣到澳洲玩的朋友也可以到這裏玩，雖然只有四項遊樂設施有點少，但山上的風景的確引人入勝，而且那裏的購物店價錢相對市區便宜很多，紀念品，食物甚至蜜糖的種類也很齊全。 之後一天就是跟學校安排去參觀電視台。下午的時候我們在前往藝術博物館的途中走過了一個非常漂亮的公園。但可惜的是，時至今日我仍然未知道該公園的名字🤦🏻‍♀️只知道它很漂亮，很舒服，讓我流連忘返不想再繼續行程。參觀完博物館，我們的下一站便是聖瑪利亞大教堂。沒有任何信仰的我，逛了一圈後也覺得它比起一座建築物更像一件藝術品。看着教堂門外有數對情侶再拍結婚照，我也憧憬着自己的將來😂😂。 第四天，我們參觀了悉尼大學，也按學校的安排參觀了一間世界著名的公關公司。由這時開始，我們可以自由購物的時間就越來越充裕了😆 第五天，我們參觀了紐卡索大學並住進了農場。那個農養了幾種動物，包括雞，鴨，兔，還有很多很多草泥馬，分別有白色和黑色的成年的和年幼的。我們每人都有一包草泥馬的飼糧可以餵食，但草泥馬是恐怖的生物，牠會反芻又會打噴嚏，弄得餵飼的人一身髒。幸運的我並沒有被牠們弄髒，但心卻被折磨得好累。(我才不會告訴你，我餵牠們的時候因為害怕所以瘋狂尖叫💩)那天晚上，我們走出小屋，看著那一片星空真的好想將它帶回香港。我用iPhone嘗試將這美景拍下來，滿天星星當中，只有三顆能出現在相片裡🤦🏻‍♀️我只好放棄，只用朋友的相機，拍出這張發上來的相片。 先發一部分，餘下的4月之內會發完。 感謝大家久等🙏🏻 #Australia#Sydney#Newcastle#SydneyHarbourBridge#SydneyOperaHouse#Darlingharbour#BlueMountain#MuseumofContemporaryArtAustralia#StMarysCathedral#TheUniversityofSydney#TheUniversityofNewcastle#farmstay

Tonight I interrupt my daily scheduled photographs to post some quiet moments captured yesterday. . Sometimes being surrounded by people can be exhausting for me, so exhausting that it drains all my energy. One thing which rejuvenates and recharges my 'batteries' is quality time alone. . Yesterday I devoured a scrumptious brunch at @badmannerthymes (if you know me, you know this place has my heart, lol), watched Power Rangers the movie and aimlessly wandered around Sydney chasing light, capturing moments and conjuring ridiculous back stories about the people I saw. . I ended my day with a hot chocolate in a cafe whilst journaling amongst the bustling sounds of people filling the air on a Saturday night, and enjoyed my train ride home listening to the Spirited Away OST. . I wonder who these two people are? What do you think their story is? First date? Best friends? Maybe even siblings? (Which would be pretty awkward since I thought they were dating, hah.) . More photographs in my story for the next 24 hours! 🤙🏾

CARROT STRETCHES! 🥕🥕 Carrot stretches are a great way to get your horse to bend and stretch out any tight muscles! They are also ACTIVE stretches which means they are safe to do anytime- why is that different from other stretches? Active or dynamic stretches -  can be performed any time with even on a cold horse. Passive stretches (where you physically help the horse into the stretch), can cause damage to soft tissues if performed on a cold horse. Always perform passive stretches (if at all) after your horse is sufficiently warmed up. (E.g., after the warm-up phase of your workout.) Over time your horse will become more flexible and will also help to prevent injuries.... On Thursday night my teachers Sat Sarbat and Sat Mukh shared their incredible wisdom and light as they taught us a workshop tapping into our authentic selves. We worked hard and my abs sure felt it the next day as I made my way to the stunning KYC Northern Beaches studio in Brookvale to be graced by the ethereal Jai Jagdeesh. Wow! This lady is from another realm, an angel walking this earth. She taught us a workshop on tapping into our intuition and releasing childhood trauma whilst she sang the mantras with a voice that can only be described as sublime! I was on such a high come Saturday morning I was flying!  I will be away for the next couple of weeks and Yogi Maya will be covering my classes. de Argel La kasba de Argel es un ejemplo de medina único en su género. Está emplazada en uno de los más bellos paisajes costeros del Mediterráneo, desde el que se dominan los islotes donde los cartagineses instalaron una factoría en el siglo IV a.C. Okay so I have to agree that I'm human like everybody else and I do have binge day weekends once in 3 months. I always weigh myself the next day after binging primarily because I'm an idiot,  and that what possible affect it could  bring on my body mass index after eating junk food all day long for 3 days.Now we all know that all of it is water retention from binging cause it's impossible to gain 3 to 5 pounds of "fat" in 3 days,  and in relation to this I've promised myself not to check the scale until the next 5 weeks knowing that i'd cry without weighing myself at least  once a week. It's not because I wanna try something new ,but because scale isn't the most accurate method of tracking progress. I mean I could be off cheat " days"for a long while and my body could be toning a lot more than the scale shows me. I've got the mirror and I've got a measuring tape too so how about I just FUCK the scale and live a beautiful life full of balance and enjoyment. Cheat meals are important for your mental health and they really help you in keeping on track but it's the cheat "days" that can fuck your progress up so ummmmm avoid them and the scale 🤔🤔🤔🤔 Anyways , your Monday lesson is to throw your scale away and give way to reliable methods of tracking progress and I.e. progress photos and measuring yourself. Have a fantabulous Monday!! 😆😆💪🏼💪🏼💪🏼💪🏼

✔ Why are we in such a hurry?  Most of us spend a lot of time feeling rushed and distracted. Living a fast everything. Our minds get filled with anxiety, restlessness and unease, living often in the past or worrying about the future, and we miss enjoying the moment we're in, the only moment we have, the present. Mindfulness can help us live a much more conscious and fulfilling life right now. Here are a few tips to bring your awareness back to the present: + Become aware of your breathing + Notice your emotions, thoughts and physical sensations, don't act on anything. Just accept and be with things exactly as they are, without judgement + Feel your feet on the floor and become aware of your environment Much Love,  Daniela xx #bombonmassage #daily #tips #love #life #behappy #takeyourtime #enjoy #awareness #mind #mindfulness #relax #sydney #wellness

No idea what to cook for dinner?  What about this hearty & delicious spinach artichoke stuffed chicken!  A trip to #PrydeMeats & you'll be able to put this on the table TONIGHT!  Recipe INGREDIENTS Chicken: 1kg boneless, skinless chicken breasts  2 tablespoons Italian seasoning 1 teaspoon mild paprika  salt and pepper to season  SPINACH ARTICHOKE DIP: 120 g frozen spinach, thawed 250 g block cream cheese at room temp 170 g bottled or canned artichoke hearts in brine, finely chopped* ½ cup shredded mozzarella cheese ¼ cup finely grated parmesan cheese 1 tablespoon minced garlic Salt to taste  OPTIONAL CREAM SAUCE: Remaining spinach / artichoke dip 1 cup milk (skim, 2% or full fat)  INSTRUCTIONS 1. Place each chicken breast on a flat surface. Season both sides of each breast with the Italian seasoning and paprika. With your hand supporting each piece, cut a slit or pocket about ¾ quarter of the way through, being careful not to cut all the way. 2. Squeeze any and all excess liquid out of the spinach. Discard the water released. In a medium-sized bowl, combine the spinach, cream cheese, artichokes, mozzarella, parmesan and garlic; mix well to combine. 3. Fill chicken 'pockets' with 1-2 tablespoons of the spinach artichoke dip, spreading evenly. Reserve the leftover dip for the optional cream sauce, or see notes for other ideas! 4. Seal with two or three toothpicks near the opening to keep the dip inside while cooking. 5. Heat 1 tablespoon of oil in a skillet (or non stick pan) over medium-high heat. Add the chicken and fry until golden. Rotate and fry on the other side, covering pan with a lid, until cooked through, (about 6 to 7 minutes per side). Transfer chicken to a warm plate to make the optional cream sauce. 6. Pour milk into the skillet / pan and bring to a simmer. Add in the remaining dip, and stir until sauce is combined and thickened. Add the chicken back into the pan and serve immediately!  #Recipe

Всем привет 👋 Сегодня я вас познакомлю с человеком, который рассказывает вам о стране, в которой мечтают побывать практически все, кого я знаю и не знаю. Знакомтесь, лицо, мозг и пальцы этого профиля - я! Зовут меня Алина и живу я в Австралии. По гороскопу я Близнецы и этим многое объясняется. Расскажу вам несколько фактов о себе, уверена вам интересно 💁🏻 🍬 Именовала меня бабуля. Глянула на меня и сказала "Назовём Алька" (Аля). А папуля явно посчитал, что он же больше участвовал в моём производстве и прав у него тоже больше. В итоге, имя в свидетельстве о рождении папуля записал одно, а называть меня продолжали все Аля (сокращенное от Алина). Потом пришлось менять документы, долго и нудно, чтобы в паспорте было Алина. Спасибо, папуля, за нескучное детство и юность. Я тебя люблю ❤ 🍬 Дедуля мой много лет работал на турбазе на Азовском море. Ну тут сразу понятно, где я проводила всё лето. А что хочет девочка, которая не вылазит из моря целыми днями? Правильно, стать русалкой. Не стала. Более того, приобрела сильную морскую болезнь. 🍬 Я ребёнок советского союза. На половину украинка, на половину русская. Я была октябренком и пионером, но ни разу не была в пионерском лагере. Помню как я утюжила пионерские галстуки, гордо их носила, романтика. 🍬 У меня есть бывший муж. Первая моя мысль при первой встрече была "Ну и придурок". А потом нагрянула любовь. Но не сложилось. Я замуж вышла по любви, а счастье обрела в разводе - это мой случай. Благодарна ему за то, что привёз меня в Австралию. Искренне желаю ему счастья. 🍬 Я родилась 6го числа, 6го месяца в 6 ч. вечера. Моё счастливое число 13. В эту дату у меня свершаются важные дела. Мой бойфренд тоже родился 6 июня. . 🙋🏻Кто угадает, как меня назвал папа, тот получит открытку из Австралии 🇦🇺 . "Can you handle the 'lag' between buying your new house & selling your old house?" In a perfect world, you would have a buyer for your current home before buying another, but it doesn't always happen that way. If you've found your dream home but haven't sold your existing property yet, we can help you explore your different options. You may also need to speak to your lender to see if you can afford a "bridging loan." Because there are so many variables, it's important to connect with a reputable and experienced real estate agent to discuss your options. A good agent should be able to advise you on the best way to sell to achieve your goals or whether or not to buy a property first.  Are you looking to take the stress out of upsizing? .I still personally think that the bravest act on earth is telling someone dear to your heart how much you love them -keeping in mind that this person may not be having the same feelings towards you, or at least not in the same intensity- and putting your ego aside, the ego ruins everything.  Tell your loved ones how much they mean to your heart right now while you're brave enough for you may not gather the courage you need later, and when everything fails at least you told whats in your heart, at least you were simple and bold enough.  We always rant about how complex life is, or -to be precise- how people complicate everything, how its supposed to be simple, how we need that much of a simplicity, and I personally think its time to practice your own teachings, putting all your cards on the table. ***Progress is rarely linear***⠀ ⠀ There's always going to be ups and downs on the journey to your ultimate goal.⠀ ⠀ If your goal is weight loss, you'll rarely see a consistent drop on the scales week in week out.⠀ ⠀ Some weeks you might lose a couple of pounds, the next you won't lose any. You might even gain a pound or two...⠀ ⠀ Accept that all weeks won't be perfect. ⠀ ⠀ Be prepared for weeks that go perfectly but don't make any impact to the scales.⠀ ⠀ Being aware of the up and down nature of weight loss is VERY important to long term progress.⠀ ⠀ Don't beat yourself up if things don't go to plan every week.⠀ ⠀ Stick to your plan, roll with the punches and track the general trend.⠀ ⠀ #training #fitness #health #progress #linear #fatloss #weightloss #fatlossjourney #fitspo #fitsporation #goalsetting #scales #scaleweight #personaltrainersydney #personaltrainerbondi #sydney #sydneylife #australianfitness

Les Touareg algerien (Targui au singulier) sont des descendants de Berbères métissés qui furent chassés des régions du Nord vers le XIe siècle. Installés dans le désert, ils se spécialisèrent dans l'élevage et le commerce caravanier entre les grandes oasis. Après plusieurs siècles de nomadisme, les « hommes bleus », appelés ainsi à cause de la couleur de leurs vêtements, ont fini par se fixer dans les villes sahariennes comme Tamanrasset ou Djanet en Algérie ♛ #Algeria #travel #traveling #art #arts #artwork #vacation #visiting #instatravel #instago #instagood #happy  #love  #photooftheday #beauty #travelling #tourism #tourist #London #sydney #newyork #instatraveling #travelgram #travelingram #paris #spain #dubia #Tokyo #Pékin #russia

A year ago or so I went virtually paperless at work. I've sensed my memory is fading a bit and I suspect it's because I use less pen and paper which has been shown to help retention. Today I re-introduced pen and paper again (in part - to mind map in meetings) and I've already found I remember more from my meetings through the day as I wrote stuff down instead of just thumbing it electronically. Interesting first day result. Has anyone found the same experience? Memory decrease with less writing?

Some of the goodies from the high tea on Sunday ☺☕️🍰🥂🍮How did I find my first ever hight tea do you ask? Nice! It's definitely not lunch - you feel full for a little while from all the delicious deserts, small canapés and tea, but eat a good breakfast or lunch before attending, so you dont go mental on the sugar high (and then that awful low lol)... Big plus for the sweets and canapés being a decent size! I would have liked to try different types of tea, but it seems that English Breakfast was the standard (I guess high teas are an English invention after all 😉) and I didnt want to be fussy (you know me!) 🙄As it was a little fancy and all, you had to catch a waiter to have your tea cup refilled. The atmosphere was super relaxed and the perfect weather added to the ambiance. It is a little pricey, but for a special occasion, it is lovely. Id love to visit their 'standard' cafe for lunch one day (you sit out on the patio instead of in the tea room). ☺👌☀️🌻🥂🌷🐝 #vauclusetearooms #vauclusehouse @vauclusehousetearooms #hightea #teatime #tealover #sydneyeats #sydneylocal #sydney #latergram #instafood #delicious #sweets #treatyoself #sweettreats

Good morning from Australia 💗 Tuesday here, Monday in the US - time for some motivation 💪🏻 On the left you can see me back in 2013, signing up to gyms every couple months, doing some cardio 3x/week and giving up after a month. I ALWAYS used to find an excuse, "Too busy, it's just not my thing, my metabolism is slow" etc. Who are we fooling with these excuses? OURSELVES. Are we happy after finding nonsense reasons for not giving our best? NO. Whatever you're doing, face the truth and write down what you should do differently do get closer to your goal. Are you currently doing it? If not: Start now, today! Not tomorrow, next week, next year. You know what you need to do! We don't have unlimited time, we have this one life, so go and be the best version of yourself TODAY! Make yourself proud 💝 Love you, peeps. WARNING - this is a long one.... UBER EXCITING ANNOUNCEMENT: You may have guessed from my posts so far that I have a ginormous travel bucket list -domestic and international. The world is an amazing place filled with wonder and unknown there's so much to explore and discover. When you travel you learn, gain perspective, and fall in love with people, places, and things you could have never imagined. I don't love using the the term 'regrets', but the one thing I wish I had done in college is study abroad and be immersed in another culture. So here it goes, for the month of May I'll be going to BALI (!!!!) and a then weeklong night cap in Sydney. I'll be working from @hubudbali on marketing and branding projects and developing some new wellness programming and workshops all while meeting new people, discovering opportunity, and absorbing the mindful culture. Oh yeah, and I'll be eating everything I can get my hands on and hopefully have lots of hands on me via massage 💕💁💃 I feel incredibly fortunate to be able to do this and am insanely nervous and beyond excited. I'll be chronicling my adventure here and on my soon to launch website along with my regular style foodie, health nut, life posts. Over the past few years I've done all types of travel from budget to splurge and have learned some really valuable lessons and tips that I'll be sharing as I go. Let me know what you want to know 😘 #bali #sydney #aroundtheworld

[Cali-baja Fish Taco Tuesday] 📍Sydney 🐟🐟🐟 Fasting from meat during lent is common practice for many Christians. But why do this... The purpose of fasting is not to "give up" things, nor to do something "sacrificial." The purpose of fasting is to learn discipline, to gain control of those things that are indeed within our control but that we so often allow to control us. In our culture especially, food dominates the lives of many people. We collect cookbooks. We have an entire TV network devoted to food [the "Food Channel"]. We have eating disorders, diets galore, weight loss pills, liposuction treatments, stomach stapling -- all sorts of things that proceed out of the fact that we often allow food, which in fact itself cannot possibly control us, to control it. We fast in order to gain control, to discipline ourselves, to gain control of those things that we have allowed to get out of control. Giving up candy -- unless one is controlled by candy -- is not fasting. It is giving up candy, or it is done with the idea that we fast in order to suffer. But we do not fast in order to suffer. We fast in order to get a grip on our lives and to regain control of those things that have gotten out of control. Further, as we sing during the first week of Great Lent, "while fasting from food, let us also fast from our passions." Acacia Flat Campground, Lake Yarrunga, Kangaroo Valley, NSW, Australia 🏞 📷: @explaurs ❕ How To Get There: From ✈SYD 1hr49mins 🚗 via Hume Motorway, drive north out of Kangaroo Valley Village on the Moss Vale Road. Just after Hampden Bridge turn left onto Bendeela Road. This becomes Jack’s Corner Road at Bendeela Pondage and then turns into a dirt road (although it is often passable in a 2WD vehicle). Continue on Jack’s Corner Road until you see a parking bay on the left for 3-4 cars next to a fire trail. Be sure to choose the fire trail rather than one of the private driveways which are marked. Follow fire trail and head downhill. After 100m go around a National Parks locked gate and continue to follow fire trail to campsite. It is around a 1.6km hike from the dirt road. ❕ #localitesSYD TIP: : There is a fire pit and one drop toilet at the campground. More facilities are available in the town of Kangaroo Valley including public toilets and shops for basic groceries.
