the latest feat. @concreteplayground 🔥 | thanks for this epic write up Quinn Connors @quinntessences ❤️ | "Some days you feel like putting together a vaguely cohesive outfit and getting dressed to leave the house; others, not so much. If you're more familiar with the latter, let us introduce you to Willa & Mae, the New Zealand label that's attempting to make it acceptable to wear your pyjamas in public.  Well, your designer pyjamas, anyway. This winter, the sleepwear-turned-lifestyle label makes its foray into Australia with ultra comfortable, effortlessly elegant pieces that are designed to be worn out of the house. Having landed in Australia in February, Willa & Mae's winter 2017 collection is available to purchase from March 31, and fundamentally functions as your new excuse to wear PJs in public and not look like a grub.  Creative director Jane Mow brings her background in menswear tailoring and styling to the brand, creating an androgynous line of highly elegant jammies. Navy, cherry and suiting stripes take shape in the old-world style of men's silk pyjamas, while long slip dresses, buttery camisoles and billowing robes recall the halcyon days of elegant women's loungewear. As piping, notched collars and cuffs evoke a certain masculinity, the luxurious silk satins maintain sensual femininity.  The foundation of Willa & Mae lies within "taking opposing ideas and asking them to play together" – like wearing your sleepwear out of the house, and still looking great. The label is guided by the unexpected through materials and patterns used, and the way its styles not only suit the bedroom, but also a night out. There's a Dr Jekyll and Mr Hyde relationship happening; on the one hand you have the sharp, feisty trendsetter Willa, and, on the other, there's Mae, keeping things grounded as the elegant, subdued yin to Willa's yang " - Concrete Playground, AUS | SEASON 4. willaandmae.com #willaandmae #madeinnewzealand @omgfive

Все чаще натыкаюсь на мнение, что мечтать, мол, вредно, надо ставить цели и идти к ним. На одних мечтах далеко не уедешь. 🙆🏽🤔 Я вот согласна лишь с тем, что ТОЛЬКО мечтать мало, это безусловно, но не мечтать вовсе 🙅🏽, с этим я не согласна и вот почему.  Мои мечты являются мотивом к действиям. Все мои цели, так или иначе, это следствие мечт🙌🏼💫 Если я мечтаю объездить весь земной шар, то это мотивирует меня больше узнавать о странах, больше работать и на чём-то экономить, а целью будет, например, накопить на поездку по нескольким городам одной страны ( рандомно) Я думаю принцип ясен.  Мне кажется, что люди, которые не мечтают, в глубине души несчастны. Возможно со стороны они кажутся вполне счастливыми и довольными жизнью, но где-то в недрах их души, это не так. Поэтому они чаще и являются теми самыми скептиками, которые ни во что не верят 💁🏽Возможно, это мнение ошибочно. Не претендую на истину в последней инстанции.  Поэтому мечтайте, визуализируйте свои мечты, мотивируйте сами себя на действия. Не смотрите на других и на чужой опыт🙏🏻 Впустите немного чудес в свою жизнь 🙌🏼💫 #australia #sydney

#R1 - 押忍!!! Today we're featuring the creative Ramens from Chef Yoshi at Tamageta-ya, starting with the Miso Pork Ramen!  I actually got this on Valentine's Day but I still remember how it tasted! Note that this is not a Ramen shop so there's some things that are slightly off (which I'll get to). The noodles I had with this were thick and curly, and slightly too soft (but I've had it again and it was fine next time around). The ramen is packed with toppings including onion, menma (メンマ; bamboo shoots), negi (葱, spring onion), thin-hot-pot like slices of pork, moyashi (もやし; bean sprouts), onsen egg (hidden under all the toppings), slices of green onion and chilli to top it all off. The highlight was the Miso broth, which consists of 5 different types of Miso and a bonito based soup. This tasted very, very similar to Wok and Noodles Miso Ramen so coming from a non-Ramen shop it's very impressive.  Given the limitations of not being able to use Ramen specific ingredients like chashu, nitamago, or custom noodles, this Miso Ramen is still impressive.  TL;DR - soft noodles, lots of toppings, miso broth very similar to Wok and Noodles. Score: 🍜🍜🍜⭕️⭕️👍 Ramen: Miso Pork Ramen Style: Shio/Seafood Broth: Chicken Price: $13.80 AUD Shop: From Tamageta-ya, 5/197 Military Rd, Neutral Bay NSW 2090.  #RamenWithFriends your next Ramen and get involved! Что Reebok - это международная компания по производству спортивной одежды и аксессуаров 🎒 В 1895 году Джозеф Вильям Фостер становится членом Клуба любителей бега 🏃🏻‍♀️ Вместе с интересом к бегу растёт и его желание пробрести качественную спортивную обувь 👟 Небогатый ассортимент предлагаемой обуви и отсутствие производителей , способных помочь ему осуществить мечту об удобной обуви сподвигли его произвести такую пару самому 👆 И вот появились первые беговые туфли "Фостер" на шипах 👉На сегодняшний день Reebok - один из крупнейших рекламодателей , в основном компания заключает контракты со звёздами НХЛ и НБА, также осваивается и на футбольном рынке 🏒🏀⚽️ А ведь все начиналось с пары беговых "Фостеров"...✨🌟 #аннакузнецова#annakuznecova#fitness#trainer#nutritionist#coach#trx#kettlebell#yoga#healthyfood#lifestyle#fit#reebok#reebokrunning#history#siberia#sibvaleo#siberianhealth#siberia#tomsk#russia#moscow#spb#krasnodar#almaty#ny#sydney#follow#followme#

DO YOU WANT TO GO AIRSIDE AT SYDNEY AIRPORT IN THE NAME OF CHARITY?? If the answer is Yes, read on:  Sydney Airport will this month offer an exclusive airside adventure to raise funds for super charity NSW Kids in Need.  The behind-the-scenes tours will take place on Sunday, 30 April as part of the World’s Largest Open House event, launched in 2015.  Sydney Airport General Manager Corporate Affairs Sally Fielke said this special event gave members of the public the chance for a rare glimpse behind the scenes of Australia's international gateway airport, while supporting kids in need across NSW. “This is a fantastic opportunity to come together as a community to support six children's charities – while also taking part in a once in a lifetime experience,” Ms Fielke said. “Our airside adventure will give people a whole new view of the airport, highlighting the work that 29,000 people across 800 different businesses on the airport do every day to keep the airport running.” LINK IN MY BIO TO PURCHASE YOUR TICKETS! Diamond earrings expected to sell for £55 million - making them the world's most expensive pair! A pair of odd earrings are set to sell for the highest ever price when they go up for auction next month. Experts described the stones as being in a "class of their own", with the pink earring named Artemis and the blue, Apollo.  Apollo is a 14.54 carat vivid blue diamond which has been cut and polished into a pear shape. Artemis is a 16 carat fancy intense pink diamond. Both gems are phenomenally rare, with less than 0.1 per cent of diamonds having any blue in them.  An "infinitesimally" small percentage of those is graded Fancy Vivid Blue like Apollo.  The pink and blue earrings were unveiled in London by Sotheby's which will be auctioning them on May 16 in Geneva. Read more on mirror.co.uk

So what’s the best milk temperature when making a flat white, latte or cappuccino? Purists and competition judges like it between 55-60 degrees celsius so they can identify all origin nuances. But most people like a hot cup of coffee and will enjoy it between 60-70 degrees celsius. When steaming your milk do not hold your hand to the side of the jug the whole time. Gently tap the jug with your hand, this way your hand won’t burn and you can make a better judgement of temperature. Otherwise, you will end up switching off the milk steaming process too early because your hand will be too hot. The key to make sure the milk is hot enough, is when your hand starts to get really hot, count to 3 in your head then turn off the steam.  This should heat your milk to 60–70 degrees celsius. If you’re a purist, warm the milk until your hand is hot, then turn off the steam. This should heat your milk to 55-60 degrees celsius. A way to get it exactly right is to use a thermometer. There’s no shame in using a thermometer if it’s going to deliver you perfect milk every time. Wow.  Simply, wow.  Just read the description on this incredibly unique #horologicalmasterpiece.  Description/photo: Touch of Modern.  The World's First Liquid Metal Display Watch:  Successfully founded on Indiegogo by Japanese designer #yasushikimura, SEAHOPE is a revolutionary design house that has released over 50 proprietary watch models. The newest iteration is the first-ever watch with a true liquid metal display. The metal within the watch dial morphs and changes shape as time passes, creating a completely unique and unconventional way to tell time aesthetically.  Join a revolution in watch design and chemical intelligence, with the SEAHOPE Liquid Metal Watch. Taking cues off everything from Salvador Dali to Terminator 2, SEAHOPE has created a new breed of metal that they call "#metallium". They studied it, learned to program it, and found a way to integrate it into a gorgeously sleek stainless steel wristwatch.  The mobile beads of molten metal freely morph and change shape as you move, like a tiny lava lamp on your wrist - but they always come to a stop at the correct hour and minute position when held at rest, with the minute hand smaller and longer than the hour hand.  The watch is water-resistant up to 30 meters, and is backlit so that you can see the time in the dark, and create an incredible glowing effect. This special version has also been chemically altered to make the liquid metal a rich, cobalt blue." Price: $249.99/$259.99 depending on style. On time♡ . 우리는 자신의 시간을 정해놓고 산다 . 그것을 스케쥴(schedule) 이라고 한다 . 재밌는 사실은 스케쥴표의 시간은 정확히 써있고 그 시간은 변동이 없는데 어떠한 사람에게는 변칙적으로 수정이 된다는것이다 . 쉽게 말해 정해진 시간을 잘 못지키는 사람들이 있다는 말이다 . 그들에게는 '머피의법칙' 처럼 약속한 시간 바로 직전에 차가막히고 또는 집이나 일터에 일이 생겨 약속시간에 짧게는5~10분 길게는 30~1시간 까지도 늦는다 . 왜 그럴까 .  시간의 중요성 그리고 자신의 신뢰도가 얼마나 하락하는줄 몰라 반복하는 우둔한 모습이다 . 나쁜습관을 몸이 베이게 하는것은 그리 어렵지 않다 그 기본은 나의 모습이되고 시간을 황금처럼 쓸 수 없게된다 . 당신에게 맞춰진 스케쥴에 살지말고 정해진 스케쥴에 맞춰진 당신을 만들어 살아라 . #스케쥴 #신뢰 #시간 #황금
